According to last year's Mpumalanga road safety campaign statistics, over 40% of accident casualties were pedestrians. JOHANNESBURG The Mpumalanga community safety MEC has lambasted pedestrians who go to taverns at night and end up jay walking on highways which leads to them being run over by cars.According to last year's Mpumalanga road safety campaign statistics over 40% of accident casualties were pedestrians.Spokesperson Joseph Mabuza said, During last year s festive season we lost many people, especially pedestrians. 